Parartemia
species have a reduced or absent 11 th thoracopod, but of the described species only P. e x t r a c t a
Linder, 1941
and P. z i e t z i a n a also have it reduced to a stub bearing few setae; it is easily distinguished from both of these species by its simple brood chamber (cf. large lobes in both other species) and its 10 th and 11 th thoracic segments being neither contracted (
P. zietziana
) or expanded (
P. extracta
). Its eggs are not distinct microscopically (but SEM studies have not been made).

